Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Grupo Aval, Grupo Suramericana

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-02-28T21:13:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-grupo-aval-grupo-suramericana.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index increased 1.8 percent to 15,008.36, while
the Colcap Index gained 2.2 percent to 1,750.97.    Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores  SA (AVAL CB) advanced 2.6
percent to 1,575 pesos. Colombia’s biggest financial holding
company is considering making additional purchases in the
financial industry in Central America and the Caribbean,
Chairman Luis Carlos Sarmiento told La Republica daily.    Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA  (GRUPOSUR CB) climbed
4.4 percent to 35,400 pesos, the biggest jump since Sept. 1. The
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank started trading on the
Mercado de Valores Latinoamericano, or Latibex, today.    Bancolombia SA  (PFBCOLO CB) jumped 2.2 percent to 27,100
pesos.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN CB) rose 1.7 percent to 2,440 pesos. The
Colombian state-controlled power producer said fourth-quarter
profit more than tripled to 201 billion pesos ($105.4 million).    Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA  (FABRI CB), Colombia’s
biggest textile maker and exporter, gained 2.6 percent to 31.20
pesos. Colombia’s peso fell to a two-week low after the central
bank said it will buy dollars daily in the local market for at
least three more months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
